Hooli Announces Fourth Quarter and Fiscal Year 2021 Results

    MOUNTAIN VIEW, Calif. – February 1, 2022 – Hooli Inc. (NASDAQ: HOOL, HOOLI) today announced
financial results for the quarter and fiscal year ended December 31, 2021.

Gavin Belson, CEO of Hooli, said: “Our deep investment in AI technologies continues to drive
extraordinary and helpful experiences for people and businesses, across our most important products. Q4 saw
ongoing strong growth in our advertising business, which helped millions of businesses thrive and find new
customers, a quarterly sales record for our Pixel phones despite supply constraints, and our Cloud business
continuing to grow strongly.”

Patrice Alexander, CEO of Hooli, said: “Our fourth quarter revenues of $75 billion, up 32% year over year,
reflected broad-based strength in advertiser spend and strong consumer online activity, as well as substantial
ongoing revenue growth from Google Cloud. Our investments have helped us drive this growth by delivering the
services that people, our partners and businesses need, and we continue to invest in long-term opportunities.”

Based on the provided text, here is a detailed summary focusing on the information within angle brackets:

In the given announcement, Hooli Inc., a company listed on NASDAQ under the ticker symbol HOOL, has released its financial results for the fourth quarter and fiscal year ending December 31, 2021. The company's CEOs, Gavin Belson and Patrice Alexander, shared their insights regarding these results during the announcement held in Mountain View, California, on February 1, 2022.

According to Gavin Belson, Hooli's deep investment in Artificial Intelligence (AI) technologies has led to extraordinary and beneficial experiences for both individuals and businesses through significant advancements in their key products. During the fourth quarter, Hooli experienced robust growth in their advertising business, enabling millions of businesses to flourish and reach new customers. Additionally, they achieved a quarterly sales record for their Pixel smartphones, even with existing supply constraints. Their cloud services also continued to show strong growth throughout the period.

Patrice Alexander emphasized that Hooli's fourth quarter revenues amounted to $75 billion, marking an increase of 32% compared to the same period in the previous year. This growth can be attributed to widespread increases in advertiser spending and heightened online consumer activity. Furthermore, substantial revenue expansion was observed in Google Cloud due to Hooli's continuous investments in providing essential services to users, partners, and businesses alike. Both CEOs expressed their commitment to further investments in long-term opportunities moving forward.

Please note that additional information may become available in future updates; however, at present, only the details mentioned in the angle brackets will be considered.
